LongDescription: CN609 nutplate has a removable clip for nut replacement and can be ordered in sizes ranging from 8/32" to 5/16-18" with a nut and baseplate material of A-286 CRES. This CN609 nutplate can be ordered in metric sizes.

Bonded nutplate's don't require any special tooling to install and eliminates two thirds of the holes in the structure by eliminating the attachment rivets normally required for nutplate installation. This nutplate can be ordered in metric sizes.
Dome nutplates work well in fuel tanks and with antenna installations. See other nutplate link for more information on other styles of nutplate.
Small base standoffs have a base diameter of .62" and are internally threaded. Thread sizes range from 4/40 up to 10/32 with lengths from .312" to 1.062".
CN125 standoff has a 1.25" diameter base with lengths varying from .312" to 1.602", thread sizes from 4/40 to 1/4-20". This standoff can be ordered with a stainless steel, aluminum or composite base.

ShortDescription: Standoff (2.00" dia) Very Large Base, Locking Thread

LongDescription: Small base studs are especially helpful when mounting very small components. Lengths vary from .25" to 1.5" with a base diameter of .62". This CS62 can be ordered in metric sizes.

CS125 Stud has a 1.25" diameter base with lengths varying form .25-1.50". Optional baseplate materials include aluminum or composite. Studs are externally threaded for use with such things as securing components or clamping lines and bundles without drilling holes. Stud base when bonded, has incredible holding capabilities.
